From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Amaan Qureshi <git@amaanq.com>
Date: Fri, 25 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] sched/fair: tighten POC fast-path affinity gate

cachyos/0012 gates the Piece-Of-Cake fast path in select_idle_cpu() on
`p->nr_cpus_allowed >= sd->span_weight`. The check is a count, not a
membership test: a task pinned to N CPUs in a different LLC passes the
gate (N == sd->span_weight) but its cpus_ptr does not intersect the
sched_domain span at all. select_idle_cpu_poc then returns a CPU from
the local LLC's idle bitmap, which is unmasked against p->cpus_ptr,
and select_idle_cpu's caller migrates the task there.

That breaks cgroup cpuset / container CPU pinning and SCHED_DEADLINE
admission, and trips the WARN_ON(!cpumask_test_cpu(new_cpu,
&p->cpus_mask)) in set_task_cpu when the chosen CPU is illegal.

Replace the count with `cpumask_subset(sched_domain_span(sd),
p->cpus_ptr)` — true only when the entire LLC domain is legal for the
task. Slightly more conservative (the fast path is skipped when even
one CPU in the domain is forbidden) but a per-call cpumask_subset on
typical LLC sizes is cheap, and the original check was incorrect by
construction. The masking-inside-POC alternative is a follow-up.

---
 kernel/sched/fair.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/kernel/sched/fair.c b/kernel/sched/fair.c
--- a/kernel/sched/fair.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/fair.c
@@ -7659,7 +7659,7 @@ static int select_idle_cpu(struct task_struct *p, struct sched_domain *sd, bool
 #ifdef CONFIG_SCHED_POC_SELECTOR
 		if (static_branch_likely(&sched_poc_enabled) &&
 				!sched_asym_cpucap_active() &&
-				likely(p->nr_cpus_allowed >= sd->span_weight) &&
+				likely(cpumask_subset(sched_domain_span(sd), p->cpus_ptr)) &&
 				likely(sd_share->poc_fast_eligible)) {
 			int poc_cpu = select_idle_cpu_poc(has_idle_core, target, sd_share);
 			if (poc_cpu >= 0) {
--
2.52.0
